  "text": "In their review of firm-level empirical studies of failure, [CITATION_1] confirm the common perception that a lack of management and financial planning skills are the most common causes of firm mortality. They reinforce this position by blaming the -liability of newness‖ associated with young firms on the inexperience and managerial deficiencies of the entrepreneur.",
